What websites for free allow me to create a landing page that automatically plays my video when opened
ChatGPT said:

Here are some free tools that let you create a landing page hosting your video with autoplay:

🎬 Free Platforms for Autoplay Video Landing Pages

  1. Wave.video – Offers free video landing page creation with a customizable player that can autoplay your video (usually muted) and supports adding CTAs. Loom+7YouTube+7Forum | Webflow+7Wave.video

  2. Ucraft – Free plan supports embedding videos (YouTube, Vimeo, or direct MP4/.ogg/.webm files), with thumbnail customization and autoplay control. Wave.video

  3. Carrd – Great for one-page minisites. The free tier lets you embed video via URL and includes autoplay settings for your video section. SeedProd+13Wave.video+13Reddit+13

  4. Wix – Its free builder allows direct video uploads or embeds (YouTube/Vimeo/etc.), with playback options, including autoplay and muted start. Wave.video

  5. Bitrix24 – Free plan includes building unlimited landing pages with hosted video and autoplay functionality as part of its CRM‑integrated offering. HubSpot Community+3Wave.video+3Forum | Webflow+3

⚙️ How to Autoplay Video Yourself (No-code / DIY)

If you're building your own page (e.g. HTML):

  • Embed a YouTube video using iframe parameters:
    ?autoplay=1&mute=1&controls=0&loop=1&playlist=VIDEO_ID
    This triggers autoplay (muted), hides controls, and loops Squarespace ForumStack OverflowLoom+1Vimeo+1.

  • For self-hosted MP4s, use the HTML5 <video> tag with attributes:
    <video autoplay muted loop playsinline src="yourvideo.mp4"></video> Squarespace ForumStack Overflow

📱 Note: Many mobile browsers restrict autoplay unless the video is muted and marked inline.

✅ Choosing the Right Option

ToolFree plan?Video embed/uploadAutoplay supportBest for
Wave.video✔️Upload/embed✔️ (customizable)Quick, shareable LPs
Ucraft✔️Upload/embed✔️Simple page builders
Carrd✔️ (up to 3)Embed/upload✔️Minimalist single-pages
Wix✔️Upload/embed✔️Drag-and-drop design
Bitrix24✔️Embed✔️CRM + LP combo
DIY HTML✔️Self-hosted/iframe✔️ (with code)Full control

🧭 My Recommendations

  • No coding, fastest setup: Start with Carrd or Ucraft — intuitive, free, and autoplay-capable.

  • More design flexibility: Go with Wix, especially if you want a polished layout and custom playback styling.

  • Simple and quick: Wave.video is excellent for generating a shareable video-first landing page with autoplay and CTAs.

📝 Quick Tips for Effective Autoplay Videos

  1. Mute the video — Most browsers won’t allow audio playback before user interaction.

  2. Use inline playback to avoid full-screen issues on mobile.

  3. Looping and controls: Add loop to maintain visual engagement, and hide player UI (controls=0) for a cleaner look.

  4. Page load speed: Optimize your video file size or use adaptive streaming to prevent slow loading. VimeoKit+10Stack Overflow+10mailerlite.com+10Squarespace Forum+3ConvertFlow+3SeedProd+3Wave.video

🎬 How to Compress Your Video in CapCut:

If You’re Using CapCut Mobile (iOS or Android):

  1. Open your project or import your video

  2. Tap Export

  3. On the export screen:

    • Change Resolution to 720p (or even 480p if you really need to shrink it)

    • Lower the Frame Rate to 24 FPS (optional)

    • Turn Smart HDR or High Quality OFF if it shows

  4. Tap Export and let it save to your phone

Check the final file size in your Photos app (or Files)

If You’re Using CapCut Desktop (PC or Mac):

  1. Open your video project

  2. Click Export

  3. In the export settings:

    • Set Resolution to 720p

    • Bitrate: set it to Low or Custom (800–1200 kbps is ideal)

    • Format: MP4

  4. Export it and then check the file size (under 100MB = ✅)

Once You Have It Compressed:
